SIMPLE: greasy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Greasy
<hw>Greas"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<er>Greasier</er> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<er>Greasiest</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Composed of, or
characterized by, grease; oily; unctuous; <as>as, a <ex>greasy</ex>
dish</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Smeared or defiled with grease.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With <qex>greasy</qex> aprons, rules, and hammers.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Like grease or oil; smooth; seemingly unctuous to
the touch, as is mineral soapstone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Fat of body; bulky.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Gross; indelicate; indecent.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Marston.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>Affected with the disease called
<cref>grease</cref>; as, the heels of a horse. See <er>Grease</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Great</ent>⟦br⟧
